Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cut the @potatoes{12%oz} into 1/2-inch pieces. Finely chop the @oregano{1%sprig}(finely chopped). On a #baking sheet{}, toss the potatoes with the oregano, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Place the baking sheet in the oven and roast for about ~{15-20%minutes}, until golden brown.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Remove and discard the ribs and stems from the @kale{1%bunch}, then roughly chop the leaves. Finely chop the @parsley{1%sprig}(finely chopped). Halve the @fresh pork chorizo{1}(halved lengthwise), then thinly slice into 1/4-inch half moons. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%clove}(minced).

Season the @cod fillets{2} on all sides with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}, then coat the fillets with @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Set on the baking sheet in the oven to roast for about ~{10%minutes}, until flaky and opaque.

Meanwhile, heat a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the chorizo and cook, tossing, ~{3-4%minutes} until slightly crispy. Stir in the @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, chopped parsley, half the garlic, and a pinch of lemon zest and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Set aside and wipe the pan clean.

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in the same pan over medium heat. Add the kale and cook, tossing, ~{4-5%minutes}, adding a splash of @water{splash} if necessary. Add the remaining garlic and cook for another ~{30%seconds}, tossing, until fragrant. Season with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}.

Serve the cod fillets on a bed of kale, surrounded by roasted potatoes. Sprinkle with the chorizo and panko mixture and top with a squeeze of lemon. Enjoy!